76561197995669628,Recommended,259190,18192646,"Posted: 25 September, 2015",all,Sorokonojka,"As someone who loves PS1 horror games like Resident Evil,Silent Hill,Martian Gothic,Dino Crisis,Countdown Vampires and other I also have a special place in my heart for Alone in the Dark series . The New Nightmare is very spooky game with obscure plot,dark atmopshere and traditional horror-survival gameplay with fixed backgrounds .Technical ProblemsYou may need third party software to use some controlers properly . I was able to assign all buttons to a controler but LT,RT not supported on F310 so I had to utilize Start/Back . (which is fine but not optimal) Free/Look is very hard on controler so be prepared to use mouse for some puzzles and maybe enemies on low elevation . For the most part you do not need to aim at enemies as long as you shoot in general direction .Some people can't get Part2 of this game to work which is what PS1 copies were known to do . I can only speak for myself and the game works fine for me on win7x64  . According to some folks using this game on Win 10 is a pain in the butt ( although I am not sure why people expect a game this old to work with abomination that is Win10 ) If there is a compatibility mode try that .GameplayVery similar to Resident Evil 1 when it comes to controls and game format .Fixed Backgrounds,Tank controls,puzzles and reloading from inventory - classic .Some enemies are vulnarable to effects of Light so you can sometimes save bullets by using flashLight or turning on lights in room . Also some puzzles will utilize Light effects so keep that in mind .Some enemies respawn infinitely so if you stack and looking for a puzzle solution you will eventually get hit .Navigating in this game is also a pain in the butt . There are hundreds of god damn doors ,eveything is dark and camera angles sometimes make it worse . I played for hours with no ammo because i just missed a shotgun in the shade :)There are 2 playable characters which have some unique areas sorta like Resident Evil 2 had with Claire and Leon . One of the bosses even chases you around which reminds me RE3 Nemesis .You can save the game at any point if you have a medalion ( No save room? I know right )Atmosphere and Immersive SettingsAmong all horror games on PS1 The New Nightmare was the best looking horror game having superior visual effects,textures and 3D models. Sure it looks dated now but back then it was as good as it got .Probably the most important thing for a Horror game is great atmosphere which this game has in spades .In the dark surrounded by shadows you will meet few characters and they won't bring you comfort.Walking through dark corridors not knowing what is ahead , what you need to do or if you have enough ammo to fight what is coming .The New Nightmare is truly immersive game that makes you feel alone in the worst place you can imagine . The hellish soundtrack is just the cherry on cake .On a side note I love camera angles in this game that add to gloomy mood ( if you playing as detective watch out for camera angle from the window of the house it is ♥♥♥♥en cool )Score 7/10. If you like PS1 horror games with tank controls you will feel right at home . This game is somewhat cryptic and can be pretty obscure with puzzles. Most of enviroments are very dark so it is hard to find items and navigate with respawning enemies . Intense settings,fun gameplay and beautiful backgrounds overall make up for the minor problems . Good game but you may need a guide ."
