,Recommended,259190,28849093,"Posted: 30 December, 2016",all,~oФe~,"~ NOTE: Windows 10 breaks some visuals in the Steam ver. of the game. The community has found a fix for it and the game is now playable again after some fixes. If you don't want to bother with some fixing you can buy AitD 4 from GOG as well. ~I've owned 3 different versions of this game, the original PS1 title that I got some 14 years ago, the PS2 title I bought so I didn't need to change discs and this Steam version for nostalgia and the fact I don't have the physical copies anymore. This said, I think I have some mileage with this game.I still play this game through at least once a year on both characters and, in my opinion, it's one of the better horror games of the PS1 with good soundscape, visuals and gameplay, and it still holds up (or maybe that's just me).It's a game every horror enthusiast should play at least once, and I highly recommend it to anyone who either likes horror games or old games."
76561197984574042,Recommended,259190,30251957,Posted: 28 February,all,ƥƦơơƑ,"""Alone in the Dark: The New Nightmare"" is a mild horror game wich is fun, has acceptable graphics (considering that it is from 2001) and a nice story.It has been quite entertaining to play through this title, especially because of its good level design and interesting characters. The graphics are still OK, even by today's standards. Basically, it uses the same mechanics as can be found in the original ""Resident Evil"", that is, you have pre-rendered backgrounds with animated 3D characters and items in the game world. If you want to play it on Windows 10 and want to have a higher resolution, just check the info on the Steam community. I think it will not work on newer OS if you do not fiddle a bit with it and use the fixes provided in the forum here. The setting is very atmospheric and eerie, and the rather nice-looking lighting effects add to this impression.In general, both the effects and music are good. Sometimes the disturbing music and some creature sounds are even really terrifying which is of course a good thing in a horror game.The controls are also good, except for some glitches when auto-aiming. I think the difficulty is medium. It would have been nice if there was an option to change it for those who would like to have more challenge.Characters and voiceover is also quite decent, only some of the male character's one liners and comments are a bit dull. Some might even like this as it makes the character more unique. You can also choose between the male and the female character. I have only played the man's storyline, but I think there are quite some differences when you choose the woman at the beginning.The only two real flaws to this game were occassional minor glitches with some enemies or other objects and that there are sometimes the notorious invisible walls or obstacles. So, when you run near the walls you hit an invisible boundary, even though your character is not actually touching any physical object.All in all, I would give this title a 75 % rating."
